questions.text: "I find it difficult to relax when I see something that needs improvement or fixing."
"I feel strongly that fairness and justice should be upheld as a matter of principle."
"I often feel a moral obligation to meet higher standards than I expect from others."
"I feel unsettled when things don’t meet my standards of order and correctness."
"I believe that rules, structure, and doing what’s right are essential for creating a better world."
"I feel frustrated when things or people don’t live up to the standards I hold."
"I often neglect my own needs because I feel fulfilled when I’m making others feel loved and supported."
"I feel happiest when I’m making someone else’s life easier or better, and it's appreciated."
"I sometimes feel hurt if my efforts to help others are not acknowledged."
"I often anticipate others’ needs before they even ask for help."
"I instinctively notice when someone needs support and feel drawn to help them."
"I feel a strong emotional need to be needed and valued by the people I care about."
"I feel driven to succeed and fear being seen as a failure or incapable."
"I often adjust my personality or behavior to match the expectations of others."
"I naturally detect what others value and scan for opportunities to shine and advance."
"I feel restless and unsatisfied if I’m not actively working toward something significant, or an ambitious goal."
"I measure my worth by how much I’m able to achieve."
"I feel a strong sense of purpose when I’m being recognized for what I accomplish."
"I feel most alive when I’m expressing something that reflects my unique identity and emotional depth."
"I sometimes feel like I don’t fully belong, as if there’s something missing or different about me."
"I find beauty and meaning in experiences that others might overlook as ordinary."
"I often feel a longing for something that is difficult to define."
"I dislike the idea of blending in with the crowd and look for ways to express my individuality."
"I’m drawn to exploring and understanding the deeper emotional truths behind my experiences."
"I feel the need to gather as much knowledge as I can before making decisions."
"I feel most at ease when I have the space to handle things on my own."
"I feel more comfortable observing from the sidelines than being the center of attention."
"I often feel drained when others make too many emotional or social demands on me."
"I sometimes worry about running out of energy or resources, so I carefully manage what I give to others."
"I prefer relationships with clear boundaries so I can maintain my personal space and autonomy."
"I am sensitive to any signs that someone may be unreliable, disloyal or inconsistent."
"I often seek reassurance from others to help me feel more confident in my decisions."
"I often look for signs that people or systems are trustworthy before I fully commit."
"I frequently worry about potential risks and plan for worst-case scenarios."
"I feel more confident when I have clear guidelines or authority to rely on."
"I feel most at ease when I can rely on others to be consistent and dependable."
"I crave new experiences and feel stifled by routine."
"I feel energized by imagining exciting new ideas and experiences that I can pursue in the future."
"I always look for opportunities to make life more fun, enjoyable, and full of variety."
"I feel trapped and restless when I’m stuck in a routine or restricted environment."
"I value flexibility and prefer to do things my way."
"I avoid dwelling on negative emotions and prefer to stay optimistic."
"I pride myself on being strong and independent, and I rarely let others see when I’m feeling vulnerable."
"I naturally detect weakness and strength in situations and people"
"I often take charge in situations where I feel things are out of control, to protect myself and others."
"I dislike relying on others and prefer to be in control of my own decisions and resources."
"I am the first to confront people or situations I believe are unfair or unjust."
"I respect people who are strong and direct, even if we don’t always agree."
"I tend to agree with others to avoid arguments, even if I feel differently."
"I feel most comfortable when everything around me is calm and harmonious."
"I often lose track of my own needs because I prioritize keeping peace and avoiding conflict."
"I sometimes go along with others’ preferences to avoid making waves or drawing attention to myself."
"I value maintaining stability and avoiding unnecessary disruptions"
"I feel most at ease when everyone around me is getting along and there’s no tension."
